<paragraph blockId="3.[151,517,474,500]" box="[151,517,474,500]" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,517,474,500]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="3" pageNumber="254" reason="1">
<taxonomicName authority="Westwood, 1829" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1829" box="[151,517,474,500]" class="Insecta" family="Chalcididae" genus="Brachymeria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,517,474,500]" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,309,474,500]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">Brachymeria</emphasis>
Westwood, 1829
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,545,750]" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1829" box="[151,297,545,570]" class="Insecta" family="Chalcididae" genus="Brachymeria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,297,545,570]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">Brachymeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a large genus with 308 described species worldwide (Noyes 2017), including many parasitoids of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="" authorityYear="1758" box="[151,289,581,606]" class="Insecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Lepidoptera</taxonomicName>
, some of which are important pests on various cultivated plants. For example 
<taxonomicName authority="Delvare" authorityName="Delvare" box="[1186,1436,581,606]" class="Insecta" family="Chalcididae" genus="Brachymeria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ceratoniae">
<emphasis box="[1186,1339,582,605]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">B. ceratoniae</emphasis>
Delvare
</taxonomicName>
was recently described from Iran as a parasitoid of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Zeller)" authorityName="Zeller" box="[750,1106,617,642]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Apomyelois" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ceratoniae">
<emphasis box="[750,1010,617,642]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">Apomyelois ceratoniae</emphasis>
(Zeller)
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="" authorityYear="1758" box="[1123,1265,617,642]" class="Insecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Lepidoptera</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[1277,1387,617,642]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Pyralidae</taxonomicName>
), an economically important pest of the carob tree, 
<emphasis box="[700,901,653,678]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">Ceratonia siliqua</emphasis>
L. (Delvare 
<emphasis box="[1055,1108,653,678]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">et al</emphasis>
. 2011). Some 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1829" box="[1283,1429,653,678]" class="Insecta" family="Chalcididae" genus="Brachymeria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1283,1429,653,678]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">Brachymeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, especially in the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1767" box="[351,429,690,713]" class="Insecta" family="Chalcididae" genus="Brachymeria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis box="[351,429,690,713]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group, are obligatory secondary parasitoids via other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="" authorityYear="1758" box="[1155,1308,690,714]" class="Insecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Hymenoptera</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName box="[1352,1436,689,714]" class="Insecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="254" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Diptera</taxonomicName>
(Burks 1960; Delvare &amp; Huchet 2017).
</paragraph>
